    "causal_summary": "A 10-angle read-only deep-research study seeded by the 029 model benchmark, which found that `/memory:search` scored an off-corpus term `kubernetes` good at 0.78 on a semantically unrelated doc, identical across all four models. Ten angle-diverse seats reading the live scoring, citation, eval, and command code converged on a diagnosis: this is a score-calibration miss, not an envelope-fidelity miss, and the root-cause fix is to require a lexical-grounding floor before awarding good. The verdict is provably independent of the isotonic calibration curve, so a curve re-fit is a non-fix. The study produced 12 ranked proposals across two distinct soft spots with a recommended build order, and the load-bearing claims were cross-model verified by gpt-5.5-fast, all PARTIAL core-confirmed, none refuted.",
